Preheat your #grill to high. Slice the @aubergine{1} into 1cm thick slices. Cut the @onion{1} in half through the root, peel and chop into ½cm pieces. Cut the top and bottom off the @courgette{1}, cut into quarters lengthways, then chop into ½cm chunks. Remove the core from the @yellow pepper{1} and chop into 1cm pieces. Peel and grate @garlic clove{1}(grated) and @garlic clove{1} left whole (or use a #garlic press{} if you have one). Pull the leaves from the @oregano{½}(finely chopped) stalks.

Put your aubergine slices on a #baking tray{} in a single layer and drizzle over some oil, a pinch of @salt{} and a good grind of @black pepper{}. Put under your grill for ~{8%minutes} on each side, until they are nicely browned and soft.

> Keep an eye on them to make sure they don't burn.

If they aren't soft in this time, just leave them under your grill for a few more mins. Remove and keep to the side when ready.

Whilst your aubergine cooks, make your tomato sauce! Put a #frying pan{} on medium heat with a drizzle of oil and add your onion. Cook for ~{5%minutes} until soft, then add your courgette and pepper along with a good pinch of @salt{} and a grind of @black pepper{}. Cook for another ~{5%minutes}.

When your veggies are soft, add the @tomato puree{1.5%tbsp} along with the @ground cinnamon{½%tsp}, grated garlic and oregano. Cook for ~{1%minute} more, then add the @red split lentils{50%g}, @Worcestershire sauce{1%tsp}, @vegetable stock pot{½}(crushed) and @chopped tomatoes{1%400g can}. Refill the tin(s) a third with water and pour this in too. Add a pinch of @?sugar{} (if you have some).

Simmer for ~{15-20%minutes} or until your lentils are soft. If it gets too dry, just add a splash of water. In the meantime, cut the @ciabatta{1} into 1cm thick slices.

Pop your ciabatta slices under your grill for ~{2-3%minutes} on each side, then remove. Rub the cut side of your remaining garlic clove across both sides of your ciabatta slices.

> Cheat's garlic bread!

When your tomato sauce is ready, transfer it to an #ovenproof dish{} and layer your aubergine slices on top. Spoon over the @crème fraîche{1%tbsp} and spread it out across the top. Sprinkle over the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} and add a grind of @black pepper{}.

Put your moussaka under your grill for ~{5%minutes}, or until your cheese is golden and bubbling. Serve in bowls with your cheat's garlic bread on the side and enjoy!